8.title: Rusty's Cage
8.plot: Kraig dives into a small space and comes out with huge findings like a vintage Coke machine potentially worth thousands and collectible professional sports pennants from teams that no longer exist.

1.title: Hit Pay Dirt
1.plot: Decades of outdated furniture and artwork have been piling up in an interior decorator's workspace. Everything has to go. The Garage Brothers team uncover a cast iron tub, two art-deco chairs, and a hand-painted rocking horse.

2.title: Down in the Dumps
2.plot: A single mom has a garage overflowing with junk, and it's up to Kraig Bantle and the Garage Brothers to transform it into a room where her two sons can play. Kraig's down in the dumps when they only find few trinkets and a toilet.

3.title: The Bad Side of a Barn
3.plot: The Garage Brothers will have to work until the cows come home to find any moneymakers in a cluttered barn. A brass platter, a 1960's stereo, and a kitschy turkey doll are a few of the odd items that could be trash or treasure.

4.title: Pinball Pains
4.plot: A piano, a pogo stick, and a vintage pinball machine could mean a hefty payday for Kraig Bantle and the Garage Brothers. But they're shocked when Mike, the team's appraiser, reveals the real values of these collectibles.

5.title: Disaster and Dolls
5.plot: A client urgently needs the Garage Brothers' help with a junked-up bedroom. It's up to Kraig Bantle and the team to get the space livable. While they dig into the filth, Kraig hopes moldy saddles and rare toys can turn a profit.

7.title: Car Parts and Pickpockets
7.plot: Bill's an old car guy at heart, but has no place to store his Original Shelby Mustang so it's up to Kraig Bantle and his crew to clean out this garage and convert the space into a showroom. This gig could be a huge payday.

8.title: Trophy Gold: A Lost Treasure Uncovered
8.plot: The Garage Brothers discover a bizarre mix in a client's garage, including a 300-year-old wig and a championship trophy. If these are real, they're not only the weirdest finds they've ever made, they're the most significant.

9.title: Cobwebs, Cake and Collectables
9.plot: Cleaning out a cake baker's garage sounds like a sweet gig, but Tony's not too keen on all the spiders, or getting stuck in a tree. Either way, the Garage Brothers have high hopes for a big payday after finding a German chest.

10.title: Geishas and Broken Drawers
10.plot: The Garage Brothers discover an eclectic mix of objects in a local artist's garage, but if Tony's not careful, they won't make a dime. A piece of Asian art that could be worth big bucks, if they can figure out where it came from.

11.title: Proceed With Caution: Ammo and Artwork
11.plot: Kraig Bantle disappoints the crew when he accepts an especially difficult job; profits this promising are worth the risk, but certainly not life and limb. There are boxes in this storage space that could blow the roof sky high.

12.title: First Flights: Cupid and Earhart
12.plot: A garage full of vintage toys guarantee Tony and Captain Ron will have a blast. Kraig Bantle's more concerned with the profits, or lack thereof. It's a rare book written by Amelia Earhart that could send profits sky high.

13.title: One Pad to the Next: Frogs and a Two-Ton Discovery
13.plot: Kraig Bantle expects a massive payday when he takes on a 7-garage gig, but isn't prepared for the mayhem that unfolds. The Garage Brothers make some remarkable discoveries, including a two-ton find along with a few roadblocks.

1.title: Equip with Weaponry: A Machete, a Pocketknife and a Prom Dress
1.plot: Kraig and the clean-out specialists rid a client's garage of junk ranging from machetes to prom dresses. Making a profit off this garage is tough work, but a mysterious silver briefcase could change everything.

2.title: Tool Mayhem
2.plot: A garage full of hardware is a promising gig for Garage Brothers. Even though Tony takes a blow to the head, Kraig discovers a tool worth more than $1000. The day is shaping up nicely until Kraig gets ganked.

3.title: Hockey and Race Cars
3.plot: Kraig takes on a hockey player's garage. Behind these doors are autographed cartoons, legendary hockey signatures and a signed stock-car helmet: something for almost everyone. The only question is, how much is it all worth?

4.title: An Old-School Job a Man Down
4.plot: You've never seen toys like these: piping-hot stoves, creepy dolls and strange accessories.

5.title: Throwbacks and Throwaways
5.plot: The crew plunges into a garage full of throwbacks, where they find the first-ever action hero, ancient electronics and a quirky midcentury carving. Even broken discoveries have all the markings of a major payday.

6.title: Snow, Sports and Bizarre Fluid
6.plot: Snowstorms are rare in North Carolina. But, so are the one of a kind sod, pinstriped memorabilia and a freezer full of breast milk the crew find in this garage. Dangerous conditions could spoil their amazing finds.

7.title: Basement Anatomy
7.plot: The guys plunge into a basement job littered with bizarre finds: a human head, a chemistry set and a gangster carrying case full of surprises. But a mysterious horn could make or break the job, if they can figure out what it is.

8.title: Toying Around
8.plot: Five kids turned this garage into a hand-me-down dumping ground, and Kraig struggles making a profit. Getting anything done in this garage is tough, but toys can turn a serious profit if they're vintage.

9.title: Grand Slam
9.plot: Kraig's crew dives headfirst into a garage so messy it might take days to clean. A dark and sketchy tunnel, a satanic find and a questionable cue-stick only add to Kraig's anxiety. Will he be able to recover his costs?

10.title: Garage of Steel
10.plot: Kraig expects big profits when he discovers relics from America's historic steel mills. Plus, the client's family owned an antique shop. This garage seems like a sure thing, until Tony wreaks havoc and Kraig pays the price.

11.title: Hats, Hardware and Zombie Gear
11.plot: Garage Brothers search for valuable tools, which Tony repurposes as zombie survival gear. Kraig's kicking himself for taking this job, but he has a chance to redeem himself when Tony challenges him to a friendly wager.

12.title: Flea Market Fever
12.plot: Kraig and crew help habitual flea-market pickers clean out a mismatched collection. One vintage find after another keeps the Garage Brothers busy. Will a first-edition book signed by a comic legend raise profits in Kraig's favor?

13.title: Radioactive Dj Disaster
13.plot: Kraig can't pass on a promising gig rumored to yield heirlooms and pro-grade DJ equipment. He makes a discovery so radioactive it glows green. Will profits do the same?

1.title: Too Cool for School
1.plot: Kraig and the crew clean a garage stuffed with old-school collectibles: boxes full of vintage beer cans, the first electronic handheld gaming consoles ever made, even hockey gear signed by a living legend.

2.title: Discoveries of the Century
2.plot: There's something from every decade in this junk jammed garage. This discovery contains strange tools, an antique punch clock, an impenetrable safe and an unforgettable galloping horse. It's one of the coolest jobs yet.

3.title: Trailer Treasure
3.plot: One trailer, four rooms, tons of discoveries: kitchen appliances, booming turntables, even handguns.

4.title: Knives and Knickknacks
4.plot: A thrift store fanatic filled her garage to the brim with all sorts of odds and ends: novelty knives, military knives and throwing knives make for a hair-raising gig.

5.title: Fitness Freak Out
5.plot: A huge garage presents an opportunity for huge profits when the guys find an insanely powerful spotlight, cool tools and old items from an even older tavern.

6.title: Traveler's Treasures
6.plot: Kraig and his crew discover foreign valuables from around the world. Will exotic treasures cover Kraig's costs?

7.title: Living Legends and Fake Torsos
7.plot: The crew discovers lots of autographed memorabilia and bizarre mannequins covered in body art.

8.title: Cellar's Market
8.plot: This job yields 50-year-old finds: groovy furniture, an old-school camera, even a player piano.

9.title: Picker's Payday
9.plot: Blowtorches and tobacco burners get the team fired up and a 100-year-old radio screams profit.

10.title: Mardi Garage
10.plot: A New Orleans family packed their garage full of Mardi Gras fun, an elk, and 100-year-old clocks.

11.title: Movie Mania
11.plot: Kraig's on a mission to bring home a life-sized silver superhero. An extremely rare autographed comic book cover turns heads and raises profits.

12.title: Rocks and Roll
12.plot: Rare concert posters capture moments in history and a t-shirt autographed by one of the greatest guitarists of all time make this job rock.

13.title: High Octane
13.plot: Awesome rides litter this garage: pit bikes, a motorcycle, and a strange wakeboard.

1.title: Texas Homerun
1.plot: Kraig travels 17 hours to tackle a massive job in the small town of Nocona, Texas. But there's nothing small about a 50-foot barn that hasn't been opened in a decade. There's even a jaw-dropping piece of American history inside.

2.title: High Class and Hi-Tech
2.plot: The Garage Brothers clean out an inventor's three-bay storage area stuffed with a strange mix of items, including books gilded in gold, an awesome vintage pinball machine and cool scientific gadgets. But do they work?

3.title: Target Practice
3.plot: The Garage Brothers tackle a large mess to surprise the homeowner's parents. But the real surprise is when they discover the garage is filled with items over 100 years old. A rare bow might help Kraig hit a bull's-eye.

-1.title: Trophy Gold: A Lost Treasure Uncovered

imdb.plot outline: Organization specialist Kraig Bantle and the crew from Garage Brothers, a family business based in Raleigh, N.C., offer to clean up garages, basements and attics that are out of control. Kraig and his team clear the clutter and repurpose the spaces into rooms that homeowners can enjoy. The catch? The crew takes any valuables they find and resells them, hoping to turn a profit.
imdb.title: Garage Gold
plot: Organization specialist Kraig Bantle and the crew from Garage Brothers, a family business based in Raleigh, N.C., offer to clean up garages, basements and attics that are out of control. Kraig and his team clear the clutter and repurpose the spaces into rooms that homeowners can enjoy. The catch? The crew takes any valuables they find and resells them, hoping to turn a profit.::DIY Network

In a media world of Auction and Pawn shows, we have been given a different angle. The four member team cleans garages and basements for free. The Catch is...they keep everything they clean out in hopes of selling items to pay for the job and make a profit. This is a great binge watching show.
